 (AIG) over a fifteen-year period through its involvement in grassroots research, in legal cases and in the compensation systems for asbestos-related disease.  It examines how the AIG became grassroots technicians of translocal paperwork, moving texts back and forth between periphery and center, pushing documents through the textual mazeways of the courts, medical institutions, the compensation system and various government agencies.   The book addresses rhetorical mobility and the extent to which, given the AIG’s position on the periphery, it has been able to enter the voices and interests of villagers into formerly inaccessible forums of deliberation and decision-making.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aAsbestos industryxHealth aspectszSouth AfricazKuruman. 0aAsbestos minersxPolitical activityzSouth AfricazKuruman. 0aAsbestosxLaw and legislationzSouth AfricazKuruman. 0aEvidence, DocumentaryzSouth AfricazKuruman. 0aLiteracyxPolitical aspectszSouth AfricazKuruman. 0aSociolinguisticszSouth AfricazKuruman. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / Political Advocacy.2bisacsh  aasbestos activism.  aasbestos.  aasbestosis.  aenvironmentalism of the poor.  agrassroots activism.  agrassroots literacy.  apaperwork studies.  asociolinguistics of globalization.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2020z9783110704594oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is pa